 narrow-band photometry that has been\nreported in-transit. New observations of energetic alkalis produced by the\nIo-Jupiter interaction are also presented, which illustrate that energetic\nsodium Doppler structure offers a more valuable marker for the presence of an\nexomoon than potassium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Feb 2022 14:22:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-01"}
